---
import Slide from "../../components/Slide.astro"
---

<Slide sectionTitle="Key Performance Metrics">
  <h2>Key Performance Metrics</h2>
  <p>Overview of the core metrics Lighthouse and Web Vitals report.</p>
</Slide>

<!-- LCP Section -->
<Slide sectionTitle="Key Performance Metrics" subSectionTitle="Largest Contentful Paint (LCP)">
  <h2>Largest Contentful Paint</h2> 
</Slide>

<Slide sectionTitle="Key Performance Metrics" subSectionTitle="Largest Contentful Paint (LCP)">
  <h3>What it measures</h3> 
  <p>Time until the largest visible content element (image or text block) is painted.</p>
</Slide>

<Slide sectionTitle="Key Performance Metrics" subSectionTitle="Largest Contentful Paint (LCP)">
  <h3>Why it matters</h3> 
  <p>TLCP closely correlates with perceived load speed and user satisfaction</p>
</Slide>

<Slide sectionTitle="Key Performance Metrics" subSectionTitle="Largest Contentful Paint (LCP)">
  <h3>How to improve</h3> 
  <ul>
    <li class="fragment">
      Optimize server response (TTFB)
    </li>
    <li class="fragment">
      Use CDNs for media/fonts
    </li>
    <li class="fragment">
      Preload, compress, and properly size images
    </li>
  </ul>
</Slide>

<!-- FID Section -->
<Slide sectionTitle="Key Performance Metrics" subSectionTitle="FID/INP">
  <h2>First Input Delay (FID) / Interaction to Next Paint (INP)</h2> 
</Slide>

<Slide
  sectionTitle="Key Performance Metrics" subSectionTitle="FID/INP">
  <h3>What it measures</h3> 
  <p>Responsiveness to user input. <p>
  <p class="fragment">FID measures initial delay; INP captures responsiveness over the whole page lifecycle.</p>
</Slide>

<Slide sectionTitle="Key Performance Metrics" subSectionTitle="FID/INP">
  <h3>Why it matters</h3> 
  <p>Users perceive a site as sluggish if interactions are delayed or stutter</p>
</Slide>

<Slide sectionTitle="Key Performance Metrics" subSectionTitle="FID/INP">
  <h3>How to improve</h3> 
  <ul>
    <li class="fragment">
      Break up long tasks
    </li>
    <li class="fragment">
      Code-split and lazy-load non-critical packages or modules
    </li>
    <li class="fragment">
      Offload heavy work to web workers, use scheduling APIs
    </li>
  </ul>
</Slide>

<!-- CLS Section -->
<Slide sectionTitle="Key Performance Metrics" subSectionTitle="Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS)">
  <h2>Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS)</h2> 
</Slide>

<Slide
  sectionTitle="Key Performance Metrics" subSectionTitle="Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS)">
  <h3>What it measures</h3> 
  <p>Visual stability; unexpected layout shifts during page load and interaction</p>
</Slide>

<Slide sectionTitle="Key Performance Metrics" subSectionTitle="Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS)">
  <h3>Why it matters</h3> 
  <p>Layout shifts degrade user trust and can cause mis-taps (poor UX)</p>
</Slide>

<Slide sectionTitle="Key Performance Metrics" subSectionTitle="Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS)">
  <h3>How to improve</h3> 
  <ul>
    <li class="fragment">
      Reserve space for images/iframes with width/height or aspect-ratio
    </li>
    <li class="fragment">
      Avoid inserting content above existing content
    </li>
    <li class="fragment">
      Use CSS transforms for animations
    </li>
    <li class="fragment">
      Use font-display or font-swap strategies
    </li>
  </ul>
</Slide>

<!-- FCP Section -->
<Slide sectionTitle="Key Performance Metrics" subSectionTitle="First Contentful Paint (FCP)">
  <h2>First Contentful Paint (FCP)</h2> 
</Slide>

<Slide
  sectionTitle="Key Performance Metrics" subSectionTitle="First Contentful Paint (FCP)">
  <h3>What it measures</h3> 
  <p>Time to the first painted content (text, image, or canvas)</p>
</Slide>

<Slide sectionTitle="Key Performance Metrics" subSectionTitle="First Contentful Paint (FCP)">
  <h3>Why it matters</h3> 
  <ul>
    <li class="fragment">
      Signals the first moment the user sees something rendered
    </li>
    <li class="fragment">
      Helps set expectations for perceived speed
    </li>
  </ul>
</Slide>

<Slide sectionTitle="Key Performance Metrics" subSectionTitle="First Contentful Paint (FCP)">
  <h3>How to improve</h3> 
  <ul>
    <li class="fragment">
      Reduce TTFB
    </li>
    <li class="fragment">
      Inline critical CSS
    </li>
    <li class="fragment">
      Defer non-critical scripts
    </li>
    <li class="fragment">
      Preload important resources (fonts, hero images)
    </li>
  </ul>
</Slide>

<!-- TTI Section -->
<Slide sectionTitle="Key Performance Metrics" subSectionTitle="Time to Interactive (TTI)">
  <h2>Time to Interactive (TTI)</h2> 
</Slide>

<Slide
  sectionTitle="Key Performance Metrics" subSectionTitle="Time to Interactive (TTI)">
  <h3>What it measures</h3> 
  <p>when a page becomes reliably interactive (all UI elements respond quickly to input)</p>
</Slide>

<Slide sectionTitle="Key Performance Metrics" subSectionTitle="Time to Interactive (TTI)">
  <h3>Why it matters</h3> 
  <p>A page that appears loaded but isn't responsive is frustrating for users.</p>
</Slide>

<Slide sectionTitle="Key Performance Metrics" subSectionTitle="Time to Interactive (TTI)">
  <h3>How to improve</h3> 
  <ul>
    <li class="fragment">
      Reduce main-thread work
    </li>
    <li class="fragment">
      Defer/idle-load non-critical JS
    </li>
    <li class="fragment">
      optimize bundle sizes
    </li>
  </ul>
</Slide>
